The company stated that the process to appoint a permanent CEO would continue in the interim. JOHANNESBURG - The South Gauteng High Court on Tuesday reserved judgment in the urgent application brought by former CEO Peter Moyo to interdict Old Mutual from continuing with the process to hire a permanent CEO. The company stated that the process to appoint a permanent CEO would continue in the interim. Old Mutual has been locked in a dispute with Moyo since it suspended him in May last year in relation to an alleged conflict of interest.